# HumanTextureizer — Vite + React + Tailwind

This repository is a minimal Vite React app preconfigured with Tailwind CSS and includes the `HumanTextureizer` component.

---

## Project structure (files included in this single-file code doc)

```
human-texturizer/
├─ package.json
├─ vite.config.js
├─ index.html
├─ postcss.config.cjs
├─ tailwind.config.cjs
├─ src/
│  ├─ main.jsx
│  ├─ App.jsx
│  ├─ components/
│  │  └─ HumanTextureizer.jsx
│  └─ assets/
│     └─ (empty)
├─ public/
│  └─ favicon.ico
└─ README.md
```

---

### package.json

```json
{
  "name": "human-texturizer",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "private": true,
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "vite",
    "build": "vite build",
    "preview": "vite preview",
    "lint": "eslint . --ext .js,.jsx"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "react": "^18.2.0",
    "react-dom": "^18.2.0"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "vite": "^5.0.0",
    "tailwindcss": "^4.0.0",
    "postcss": "^8.0.0",
    "autoprefixer": "^10.0.0",
    "eslint": "^8.0.0",
    "eslint-plugin-react": "^7.0.0"
  }
}
```

---

### vite.config.js

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
})
```

---

### index.html

```html
<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Human Textureizer</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="root"></div>
    <script type="module" src="/src/main.jsx"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

---

### postcss.config.cjs

```js
module.exports = {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  }
}
```

---

### tailwind.config.cjs

```js
module.exports = {
  content: ['./index.html', './src/**/*.{js,jsx}'],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

---

### src/main.jsx

```jsx
import React from 'react'
import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client'
import './index.css'
import App from './App'

createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <App />
  </React.StrictMode>
)
```

---

### src/index.css

```
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

html, body, #root { height: 100%; }
```

---

### src/App.jsx

```jsx
import React from 'react'
import HumanTextureizer from './components/HumanTextureizer'

export default function App(){
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 p-6">
      <HumanTextureizer />
    </div>
  )
}
```

---

### src/components/HumanTextureizer.jsx

The full `HumanTextureizer` component (React) is included below. It is the same implementation provided earlier in the canvas — it handles image upload, client-side canvas processing (grain, fibers, scratches, edge enhancement, warmth/vignette), sliders and download. Place that component code here verbatim.

---

### public/favicon.ico

Add any small favicon or leave default.

---

### README.md

```md
# Human Textureizer

Minimal Vite + React + Tailwind app that applies human-like textures to images client-side.

## Setup

1. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

2. Run dev server

```bash
npm run dev
```

3. Build for production

```bash
npm run build
```

## Notes
- All processing is done in-browser using Canvas APIs.
- To speed up for large images consider adding WebGL shader-based processing.
```

